  "blurb": "A private coastal estate of rare distinction on Koh Samui's unspoilt Lamai–Hua Thanon shore — two iconic villas set among dramatic granite boulders and coconut palms, with twin 20-metre infinity pools, ten sea-view bedrooms and an outdoor cinema by the sand.",
  "detail": "This pair of iconic homes sits along Koh Samui's unspoilt Lamai–Hua Thanon shoreline, framed by granite boulders, coconut palms and uninterrupted ocean vistas in a setting both dramatic and deeply serene. Bookable together as a single fully-staffed estate for up to twenty guests across ten bedrooms, or villa by villa, it is built for multi-generational escapes and refined group gatherings.\n\nEach villa is laid out as a pavilion-style composition that celebrates seamless indoor-outdoor living, with natural light and sea breezes flowing throughout — and no cookie-cutter rooms: every bedroom has a sea view and a unique layout shaped around the surrounding rock formations, each with its own freestanding bathtub. Days gather around open-plan dining rooms and high-ceilinged living rooms, then move outdoors to terraces and infinity pools (19.7 and 20 metres) with kid-friendly shallow ends, daybeds and sunset views.\n\nKayaks, SUP boards and a table-tennis table are on hand for the active; a dedicated team — villa manager, private chef, housekeeper and handymen at each villa — looks after the rest. As evening falls, chef-prepared dinners give way to cinematic nights under the stars beneath a poolside projector screen, the famous Hin Ta and Hin Yai rocks just along the coast.",
